      "id": "dd17365a003d14146919df0ce95e4e2a9ee707de",
      "message": "Node resizing (#14849)\n\n- Node height can be resized\n- Height is persistent\n- Widgets may determine whether they are fixed-height or fit the node's height through CSS\n- When a node has not been manually sized, its height is determined by the widgets it contains\n- Simplify resizable widget logic\n- Fix widgets changing size when zooming\n- Fix some `ResizeObserver` loop errors\n- New ResizeHandles API\n- Component props are stable when zooming, fixing a scalability issue\n- API handles scaling and provides updates differently, simplifying usage\n- Other node size logic cleanup\n- Simplify graph store: Remove redundant \"viz rect\" state\n- Fix a potential performance issue: Debounce rect updates that were being emitted frequently but were redundant when a `Rect` was recomputed to a new object with the same values\n\nhttps://github.com/user-attachments/assets/19fcd16d-ac73-4ef5-a764-083bf6d81517\n\nFixes #14626.",
